“Today, the situation on the ground is more stable and safe, thanks to the progress we have made in the fight against terrorism,” he said.
The government continues to rebuild the areas devastated by the terrorists in order to restore them to their normal state.
All conditions are now in place for the voluntary return of refugees to the country they were forced to leave because of terrorism and the unilateral economic measures that affected their daily lives and livelihoods.
